<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Leeds United are in talks with Dinamo Zagreb over Croatia U21 international defender Josko Gvardiol.</p>

<p>The highly-rated 18-year old has attracted attention from some of Europe’s biggest clubs while he progressed from the Zagreb’s academy to their first team. </p>

<p>Bayern Munich made enquiries in May.</p>

<p>Leeds United are in talks with Dinamo Zagreb over defender Josko Gvardiol (above)</p>

<p>The 6ft 2ins defender can play left back as well as centre back. </p>

<p>Leeds want to bolster their defence line after Brighton refused to part with Ben White following his successful loan at Elland Road last term.</p>

<p>But they have brought in Germany international centre-back Robin Koch from Bundesliga outfit Freibu </p>
